18/11/2005
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The European Council will approve the negotiation platform concerning the Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with BiH on Monday (21 November), clearing the way for talks to begin this month.
Fabrizio Barbaso, head of the European Commission's Directorate-General for Enlargement, made the announcement after his meeting Thursday with BiH Council of Ministers Chairman Adnan Terzic.
Barbaso came to Sarajevo to present the EC's progress report, prepare the groundwork for SAA negotiations, and urge local authorities to step up the implementation of reforms.
In other news, the BiH Council of Ministers appointed Igor Davidovic, former ambassador to the United States, to lead the country's negotiations on the SAA.
The other members of the team include Terzic, Mladen Ivanic, Barisa Colak, Dragan Doko, Safet Halilovic, Slobodan Kovac, Osman Topcagic and Lidija Topic.
(Dnevni Avaz, Nezavisne Novine - 18/11/05;
PBS BiH, Fena - 17/11/05)
